  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-7 Not Accepted)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (4 meeting required levels, 3 falling below required levels), 6 factors scoped-out with documented rationale. Decision is Not Accepted due to documented shortfalls in Discretization Error, Output Comparison, and Model Form — all assessed with achievedLevel below requiredLevel, with no offset claimed.",
