      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/discr-error-mrl2",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error MRL-2 acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Grid convergence index (GCI) < 5% on the primary QoI (hemolysis index) across at least three systematically refined mesh levels, with Richardson extrapolation performed and reported."
      },
      "rationale": "Mesh refinement study was conducted across three mesh levels (2.1M, 5.6M, and 11.4M elements). However, the GCI computed for the hemolysis index at the 5 L/min operating point reached 8.3%, exceeding the 5% acceptance threshold. Richardson extrapolation was performed but the asymptotic convergence ratio was not fully achieved (r = 1.07 vs. required r >= 1.3). The achieved discretization error characterization corresponds to Gradation 2, falling short of the required Gradation 3. This shortfall is not offset by compensating evidence."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/test-conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/test-conditions-mrl2",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions MRL-2 acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature) documented with measurement uncertainty and applied consistently in CFD boundary condition specification."
      },
      "rationale": "In-vitro test conditions documented in the FDA generic pump experimental dataset include inlet flow rate (2–6 L/min ± 0.05 L/min), rotational speed (2000–3500 RPM ± 5 RPM), and fluid temperature (37 °C ± 0.5 °C). These boundary conditions are faithfully reproduced in the CFD model. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/output-comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/output-comparison-mrl2",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison MRL-2 acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., normalised hemolysis index error) reported with experimental uncertainty bounds; CFD predictions fall within combined simulation and experimental uncertainty for at least 4 of 5 operating points."
      },
      "rationale": "Quantitative output comparison was performed for hemolysis index (HI) across 5 operating points. CFD predictions fell within combined uncertainty bounds at only 2 of 5 operating points; at 3500 RPM / 3 L/min, the CFD over-predicted HI by 22%, well outside the ±8% combined uncertainty band. The comparison metric was computed and reported, but the breadth of agreement does not reach the Gradation 3 threshold requiring agreement at 4 of 5 points. This shortfall directly undermines confidence in model predictive fidelity and contributes to the Not Accepted decision."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/relevance-qoi",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/relevance-qoi-mrl2",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI relevance MRL-2 acceptance criteria",
        "description": "The primary QoI (normalised hemolysis index, RH) is directly mapped to the clinical endpoint (hemolysis risk) and the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate device)."
      },
      "rationale": "The normalised hemolysis index (RH) is the direct regulatory QoI specified in FDA guidance for blood-contacting rotary pumps. The mapping from CFD-predicted scalar stress exposure to RH via the Giersiepen power-law model is documented and consistent with the intended COU. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/relevance-validation-activities",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/relevance-validation-mrl2",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Validation activity relevance MRL-2 acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Validation experiments conducted on the same pump geometry under overlapping operating conditions (flow rate, RPM) as the COU; fluid analog properties (viscosity, density) within 5% of blood surrogate used clinically."
      },
      "rationale": "Bench-top validation experiments used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry with a glycerol-water blood analog (viscosity 3.5 cP, density 1056 kg/m³), closely matching clinical blood properties. Operating points tested (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM) span the COU envelope. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/model-form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/model-form-mrl2",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form MRL-2 acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Documented justification for selection of turbulence model and hemolysis damage accumulation model, including comparison of at least two candidate model forms against experimental data with quantified selection rationale."
      },
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on prior literature for rotating machinery; however, only a single turbulence model was evaluated. No systematic comparison against an alternative (e.g., realizable k-epsilon or LES) was performed. The Giersiepen hemolysis power-law model was adopted without comparison to the Zhang or Arora models, which have demonstrated different predictive behaviour in high-shear regions. The absence of a comparative model-form evaluation limits the achieved level to Gradation 2, below the required Gradation 3. This constitutes a substantive credibility gap at the claimed COU."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/numerical-solver-error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error (iterative convergence error) is scoped out at MRL 2 for this COU. Residual convergence to 1e-5 for all equations was confirmed in all simulations, and the solver is a commercial code with documented iterative error controls. Separate quantification of solver error beyond residual monitoring is not required at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 1 guidance."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/use-error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment is scoped out at MRL 2. The simulation team consists of two senior CFD engineers with documented training records and prior peer-reviewed publications on blood pump CFD. An internal peer review of simulation setup was completed. Formal use-error quantification is not required at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 1."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/model-inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Formal model input uncertainty propagation is scoped out at MRL 2. Key inputs (geometry, fluid properties, boundary conditions) are documented with measurement uncertainty. Full probabilistic uncertainty propagation is not required at MRL 2; deterministic sensitivity runs across ±5% geometry tolerances were performed as a substitute and are documented separately."
