  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-cou1-not-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-cfd-vv-team-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Not accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 (CFD hemolysis prediction for CPB Class II device, MRL 2) is Not Accepted based on documented shortfalls in three assessed credibility factors, none of which are offset by compensating evidence. (1) Discretization Error: The GCI for the hemolysis index at the 5 L/min operating point was 8.3%, exceeding the 5% threshold required at Gradation 3. The asymptotic convergence ratio was not achieved. Achieved level 2 vs. required level 3. (2) Output Comparison: CFD predictions fell within combined uncertainty bounds at only 2 of 5 operating points. At the 3500 RPM / 3 L/min condition, the model over-predicted the hemolysis index by 22%, well outside the ±8% combined uncertainty band. Achieved level 2 vs. required level 3. (3) Model Form: Only a single turbulence model and a single hemolysis damage model were evaluated. No comparative model-form analysis was performed against alternative turbulence or hemolysis model candidates. Achieved level 2 vs. required level 3. These three shortfalls collectively indicate that the model has not demonstrated sufficient predictive fidelity to support the intended regulatory claim (identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions with RH < 1 relative to predicate device). No offset rationale is claimed. The assessment team recommends: (a) conducting additional mesh refinement to achieve GCI < 5% and confirmed asymptotic convergence; (b) extending validation to achieve agreement at ≥ 4 of 5 operating points; and (c) performing a comparative model-form study evaluating at least one alternative turbulence model and one alternative hemolysis accumulation model before resubmission.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
